An array is container object which holds a certain number of values of a single type. 
How does one make a simple array of Strings?
One must declare that you are creating an array of strings and then list the strings that you wish to be a part of the array.
What is the syntax for a 2-D array?
    static void onewordalllowercase(){
            char[][] board = new char[10][10]; // creates the array 
        board[boardX= 4][boardY= 5] = '@'; // places the '@' symbol near the middle there is no middle 
        for (int i = 0; i <= board[0].length - 1; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j <= board[1].length - 1; j++) {
                if (j < board[1].length - 1) {
                    if (board[i][j] != '@') {
                        System.out.print("☐");
                    } else {
                        System.out.print(board[i][j]);
                    }
                } else {
                    if (board[i][j] != '@') {
                        System.out.println("☐");
                    } else {
                        System.out.println(board[i][j]);
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
